\section{Discovering blocks for event sequences covering: Problem statement}
\label{p1:chap_pb}


  \subsection{generalities}

%utiliser pour justifier le découpage en frames et généraliser par un découpage par fenêtre de temps, qui nécessite uin avis d'expert
\cite{Study on Video DM} recalls that the semantic information used to identify the video events has two important aspects: (i) A spatial aspect presented 
by a video frame, such as the location, characters and objects displayed in the video frame. (ii) A temporal aspect presented by a sequence of video frames 
in time such as movements of the objects presented.